summary:
The Security Council,

Recalling previous resolutions on Iraq, 
Convinced of the need to continue providing for the civilian needs of the Iraqi people,

Adopted resolution 1447 (2002) on 4 December 2002:

1. Decides to extend the provisions of resolutions 986 (1995) and 1360 (2001) for 180 days from 5 December 2002;
2. Decides to review and adjust the Goods Review List and its implementation procedures within 30 days and thereafter conduct regular reviews;
3. Interprets references to the 150-day period in resolution 1360 (2001) as referring to the new 180-day period;
4. Requests the Secretary-General to report on Iraq's distribution of humanitarian supplies and medicine, and on the adequacy of revenues to meet humanitarian needs, at least one week before the end of the 180-day period;
5. Requests the Secretary-General to assess the implementation of the Goods Review List and submit recommendations on revisions 14 days before the end of the 180-day period;
6. Decides to remain seized of the matter.
